@Gallay

Conspicuous is an adjective and so is NOT(ice)ABLE. NOT(ice)ABLY is an adverb and would have to be clued “conspicuously”. I certainly didn’t know the rap hit immediately but the grammar agreement should have made the error clear.
Also this is something to think about when you are guessing Naticks. Put yourself in the mind of the editors. They would usually not clue DRY as part of the title of an obscure rap hit from 2022, at least not without something else in the title that would point to it—whereas DRE is a pretty famous rapper even to me and once I got it, that would make sense to me why it would be a rap title. Of course sometimes there are things which are obscure to some people but obvious to others, but I do think using this type of logic helps sometimes figuring out the answers to clues.

